# Rx Helper — Append-only decision log
#
# FORMAT:   <ISO-8601-timestamp>\t<author>\t<TYPE>\t<message>
# RULES:    (1) Append only. Never edit or delete a previous line.
#           (2) Wall-clock timestamps, IST (+05:30). Use `date -u +"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S+05:30"` if unsure.
#           (3) Authors: ruchir | bs23b014 | harshit | ruchir-agent | bs-agent | harshit-agent
#               Agents MUST suffix `-agent` so humans can tell them apart.
#           (4) Latest entry wins when in conflict with TEAMMATES sections marked FROZEN.
#           (5) Sections NOT marked FROZEN are guidance; the log only overrides FROZEN sections.
#
# TYPES:
#   DECISION   - architectural or design choice (overrides TEAMMATES FROZEN sections on conflict)
#   SCOPE-IN   - feature accepted into scope
#   SCOPE-OUT  - feature removed from scope
#   OWNER      - ownership assignment / transfer
#   EDIT       - file is being edited right now (acts as a soft lock)
#   DONE       - finished a task; clears any EDIT lock by same author on same file
#   BLOCKED    - stuck, needs help; tag who can unblock
#   PROPOSE    - suggested change to a FROZEN surface; does NOT take effect until RESOLVED
#   RESOLVE    - Ruchir's ruling on a PROPOSE; ACCEPT or REJECT with reason
#   CONFLICT   - you noticed two instructions disagree; include both and who's involved
#   QUESTION   - open question, include who should answer
#   DEMO-PREP  - demo or rehearsal note
#
# SHORTCUTS:
#   append-decision() { printf '%s\t%s\t%s\t%s\n' "$(date -u +"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S+05:30")" "$1" "$2" "$3" >> DECISIONS.log; }
#   tail -n 20 DECISIONS.log    # read recent state before making changes
#
# =============================================================================
